Changelog
=========

1.0.0 (November 7th, 2025)
-----------------------

* New: Aligned support with official Django/Python support matrix, dropping support for Django<4.2 and Python<3.8
* New: Added basic test suite
* New: Added tox for multi-version testing
* New: Formatted code with Black

0.3.8 (April 13th, 2022)
--------------------------

* Fixed: Switched from `smart_text` to `force_str` to avoid error in Django 4.0

0.3.7 (April 13th, 2022)
--------------------------

* Fixed: Remove reliance on `cgi.escape`, which no longer exists in Python 3.8
* Indicating compatibility with Python 3.7 and 3.8

0.3.6 (June 17th, 2021)
--------------------------

* Updated: The `charset` attribute on `<style>` and `<script>` is now obsolete

0.3.5 (June 17th, 2021)
--------------------------

* Indicating compatibility with Django 3.1 and 3.2

0.3.4 (April 9th, 2020)
--------------------------

* Indicating compatibility with Django 3.0

0.3.3 (January 23rd, 2020)
--------------------------

* Fixed: Relaxed dependency on six

0.3.2 (October 10th, 2019)
--------------------------

* Fixed: Django version in package requirements

0.3.0 (October 10th, 2019)
--------------------------

* New: Added compatibility with python 3.6 and Django 2.x.

0.2.5 (September 26th, 2018)
--------------------------

* Updated: Bundling `html` library to avoid installation issues with newer Python/Setuptools versions

0.2.4 (May 15th, 2018)
--------------------------

* Updated: Improved handling of missing files

0.2.0 (May 8th, 2018)
--------------------------

* New: Refactored file/path handling and added `includegeneric` template tag

0.1.0 (July 28th, 2016)
--------------------------

* New: Initial version supporting basic CSS and JS inlining from static files
